         <abstract>
            <p>EMPLOYERS of truck drivers have an important and sometimes difficult job in training their drivers to conserve the vehicles they use. One approach to this problem of training drivers to their responsibilities is presented here by Mr. Sinclair, who sets forth and elaborates on a series of "don'ts" that drivers should diligently and persistently practice.</p>
